C++Blueprint <pre><code>#include "Courier/CourierSubsystem.h"

UCourierSubsystem* Courier = GetGameInstance()-&gt;GetSubsystem&lt;UCourierSubsystem&gt;();

FCourierHandle Handle = Courier-&gt;RequestLoad(
    WeaponSoftRef,                  // TSoftObjectPtr&lt;UObject&gt; or FSoftObjectPath
    ECourierPriority::High,
    FOnCourierLoaded::CreateLambda([this](UObject* LoadedAsset)
    {
        WeaponMesh = Cast&lt;USkeletalMesh&gt;(LoadedAsset);
        SpawnWeapon();
    })
);
</code></pre> <ul> <li>Call Courier &gt; Request Load Async with a Soft Object Reference and Priority.</li> <li>Bind the On Loaded output pin to your callback event.</li> </ul>

BlueprintC++ <ol> <li>Open your Player Controller Blueprint.</li> <li>In the Components panel click Add and search for <code>GimbalComponent</code>.</li> <li>Select the component and set Default Mode Asset in the Details panel.</li> </ol> <pre><code>// MyPlayerController.h
#include "Gimbal/GimbalComponent.h"

UPROPERTY(VisibleAnywhere, BlueprintReadOnly)
TObjectPtr&lt;UGimbalComponent&gt; GimbalComponent;

// MyPlayerController.cpp
AMyPlayerController::AMyPlayerController()
{
    GimbalComponent = CreateDefaultSubobject&lt;UGimbalComponent&gt;(TEXT("GimbalComponent"));
}
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <ul> <li>Call Gimbal &gt; Push Mode on the Gimbal Component, passing your <code>GimbalModeAsset</code>.</li> <li>Call Gimbal &gt; Pop Mode to remove the top-most mode matching an asset reference.</li> </ul> <pre><code>// Activate combat lock-on camera
GimbalComponent-&gt;PushMode(LockOnModeAsset, EGimbalBlend::Curve);

// Return to default after combat
GimbalComponent-&gt;PopMode(LockOnModeAsset);
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <ol> <li>Open your Character Blueprint.</li> <li>Add Component &gt; LeanComponent.</li> <li>Set Lean Target Component to your camera or spring arm in Details.</li> </ol> <pre><code>#include "Lean/LeanComponent.h"

UPROPERTY(VisibleAnywhere)
TObjectPtr&lt;ULeanComponent&gt; LeanComp;

// Constructor
LeanComp = CreateDefaultSubobject&lt;ULeanComponent&gt;(TEXT("LeanComponent"));
LeanComp-&gt;LeanTargetComponent = CameraComponent;
LeanComp-&gt;MaxLeanOffset = 60.f;
LeanComp-&gt;LeanSpeed = 8.f;
</code></pre>

Enhanced Input (Recommended)Manual C++Blueprint <ol> <li>Create an <code>InputAction</code> for lean (Axis1D or Axis2D).</li> <li>In Details on <code>ULeanComponent</code>, assign Lean Input Action.</li> <li>Lean drives itself — no event graph wiring needed.</li> </ol> <pre><code>// In your Character or Controller's input handler
void AMyCharacter::OnLeanInput(float Value)
{
    LeanComp-&gt;SetLeanInput(Value); // -1.0 = full left, 1.0 = full right
}
</code></pre> <ul> <li>Call Lean &gt; Set Lean Input from your input event with the axis value.</li> </ul>

C++Blueprint <pre><code>#include "Manifest/ManifestSubsystem.h"

UManifestSubsystem* Manifest = GetGameInstance()-&gt;GetSubsystem&lt;UManifestSubsystem&gt;();

FPrimaryAssetId SwordId = FPrimaryAssetId(TEXT("Item"), TEXT("Sword_Iron"));

Manifest-&gt;Resolve(SwordId, ECourierPriority::High,
    FOnManifestResolved::CreateLambda([this](UManifestResolvedObject* Resolved)
    {
        if (Resolved &amp;&amp; Resolved-&gt;IsLoaded())
        {
            UItemDefinition* ItemDef = Cast&lt;UItemDefinition&gt;(Resolved-&gt;GetObject());
            EquipItem(ItemDef);
        }
    })
);
</code></pre> <ul> <li>Call Manifest &gt; Resolve Asset with a <code>Primary Asset Id</code> and priority.</li> <li>Bind the On Resolved output to your callback.</li> </ul>

BlueprintC++ <ol> <li>Open your AI Character Blueprint.</li> <li>Add Component &gt; OmniSenseComponent.</li> <li>Configure Team, Vision Half Angle, Vision Range, and Acoustic Sensitivity in Details.</li> </ol> <pre><code>#include "OmniSense/OmniSenseComponent.h"

UPROPERTY(VisibleAnywhere)
TObjectPtr&lt;UOmniSenseComponent&gt; OmniSense;

// Constructor
OmniSense = CreateDefaultSubobject&lt;UOmniSenseComponent&gt;(TEXT("OmniSense"));
OmniSense-&gt;TeamId = 1;
OmniSense-&gt;VisionHalfAngle = 60.f;
OmniSense-&gt;VisionRange = 1500.f;
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <p>Bind On Stimulus Detected on the OmniSense component in your AI Character's BeginPlay: <pre><code>[BeginPlay] → [Bind OnStimulusDetected] → [AI Event: React to Stimulus]
</code></pre></p> <pre><code>OmniSense-&gt;OnStimulusDetected.AddDynamic(this, &amp;AMyAICharacter::HandleStimulusDetected);

void AMyAICharacter::HandleStimulusDetected(const FOmniStimulusEvent&amp; Event)
{
    if (Event.SenseType == EOmniSenseType::Vision &amp;&amp; Event.Relationship == EOmniRelationship::Hostile)
    {
        AIController-&gt;SetFocus(Event.SourceActor);
    }
}
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <ol> <li>Open your door/lever/switch Blueprint.</li> <li>Add Component &gt; PerpetualAnimationComponent.</li> <li>Set Animation Asset in Details to your Data Asset.</li> <li>Set Target Component to the mesh or scene component to animate.</li> </ol> <pre><code>#include "Perpetual/PerpetualAnimationComponent.h"

UPROPERTY(VisibleAnywhere)
TObjectPtr&lt;UPerpetualAnimationComponent&gt; PerpetualAnim;

// In constructor
PerpetualAnim = CreateDefaultSubobject&lt;UPerpetualAnimationComponent&gt;(TEXT("PerpetualAnim"));
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <ul> <li>Call Perpetual &gt; Go To Stage and pass the stage name (e.g., <code>"Opening"</code>).</li> <li>Call Perpetual &gt; Advance to move to the next stage in the sequence.</li> <li>Call Perpetual &gt; Reverse to go to the configured reverse stage.</li> </ul> <pre><code>// Trigger door open
PerpetualAnim-&gt;GoToStage(FName("Opening"));

// Advance through sequence
PerpetualAnim-&gt;Advance();

// Reverse (e.g., close door)
PerpetualAnim-&gt;Reverse();
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <p>Bind to the <code>OnStageComplete</code> delegate in the Event Graph: <pre><code>[BeginPlay] → [Bind Event to OnStageComplete] → [Custom Event: HandleStageComplete]
</code></pre></p> <pre><code>PerpetualAnim-&gt;OnStageComplete.AddDynamic(this, &amp;AMyDoor::HandleStageComplete);

void AMyDoor::HandleStageComplete(FName StageName)
{
    if (StageName == FName("Open"))
    {
        // Door is fully open
    }
}
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <ol> <li>Open your Player Character Blueprint.</li> <li>Add Component &gt; ReachDetectorComponent.</li> <li>Set Detection Radius, Detection Interval, and Interact Input Action.</li> </ol> <pre><code>#include "Reach/ReachDetectorComponent.h"

UPROPERTY(VisibleAnywhere)
TObjectPtr&lt;UReachDetectorComponent&gt; ReachDetector;

// Constructor
ReachDetector = CreateDefaultSubobject&lt;UReachDetectorComponent&gt;(TEXT("ReachDetector"));
ReachDetector-&gt;DetectionRadius = 200.f;
ReachDetector-&gt;DetectionInterval = 0.1f;
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <ol> <li>Open your prop Blueprint (door, chest, button, etc.).</li> <li>Add Component &gt; ReachInteractableComponent.</li> <li>Set Interaction Mode (Instant, Hold, Smash, Rhythm) and Display Name.</li> </ol> <pre><code>#include "Reach/ReachInteractableComponent.h"

UPROPERTY(VisibleAnywhere)
TObjectPtr&lt;UReachInteractableComponent&gt; Interactable;

Interactable = CreateDefaultSubobject&lt;UReachInteractableComponent&gt;(TEXT("Interactable"));
Interactable-&gt;InteractionMode = EReachInteractionMode::Hold;
Interactable-&gt;HoldDuration = 2.0f;
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <p>Bind On Interacted on the <code>UReachInteractableComponent</code>: <pre><code>[BeginPlay] → [Bind OnInteracted] → [Open Door / Pick Up Item / etc.]
</code></pre></p> <pre><code>Interactable-&gt;OnInteracted.AddDynamic(this, &amp;AMyDoor::HandleInteract);

void AMyDoor::HandleInteract(APawn* Interactor)
{
    OpenDoor();
}
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <ul> <li>Call Relay &gt; Broadcast with a GameplayTag and an optional payload struct.</li> </ul> <pre><code>#include "Relay/RelayBlueprintLibrary.h"

// Simple broadcast (no payload)
URelayBlueprintLibrary::Broadcast(this, FGameplayTag::RequestGameplayTag("Event.Combat.MeleeHit"));

// Broadcast with a payload
FRelayPayload_Combat Payload;
Payload.DamageAmount = 42.f;
Payload.HitLocation = ImpactPoint;
URelayBlueprintLibrary::BroadcastWithPayload(this, Tag, Payload);
</code></pre>

Blueprint (Async Action)Blueprint (Listener Group)C++ <ol> <li>In your Blueprint Event Graph, right-click and search Relay Listen.</li> <li>Set the Channel Tag and Min Priority.</li> <li>Connect the On Message output pin to your handler.</li> </ol> <pre><code>[BeginPlay] → [Create Relay Listener Group] → [Subscribe (Tag, Callback)]
[EndPlay]   → [Listener Group &gt; Unsubscribe All]
</code></pre> <pre><code>#include "Relay/RelayListenerGroup.h"

// Create in your actor
ListenerGroup = NewObject&lt;URelayListenerGroup&gt;(this);

ListenerGroup-&gt;Subscribe(
    FGameplayTag::RequestGameplayTag("Event.Combat"),
    FOnRelayMessage::CreateUObject(this, &amp;AMyActor::HandleCombatEvent),
    /* MinPriority */ 0
);

// In destructor or EndPlay:
ListenerGroup-&gt;UnsubscribeAll();
</code></pre>

C++Blueprint <pre><code>#include "Sleight/SleightGameStateComponent.h"

USleightGameStateComponent* Sleight = GameState-&gt;GetComponentByClass&lt;USleightGameStateComponent&gt;();

// Start a game for two players
Sleight-&gt;InitializeGame(Player1Controller, Player2Controller, GameRulesClass);

// Deal opening hands
Sleight-&gt;DealOpeningHands();
</code></pre> <p>Call Sleight &gt; Initialize Game on the Game State Component in BeginPlay or your match initialization event.</p>

BlueprintC++ <ul> <li>Call Sonance &gt; Play Music Track passing the <code>USonanceMusicTrack</code> asset.</li> <li>Call Sonance &gt; Set Stem Weight to fade individual stems in/out.</li> </ul> <pre><code>USonanceSubsystem* Sonance = GetWorld()-&gt;GetSubsystem&lt;USonanceSubsystem&gt;();
Sonance-&gt;PlayMusicTrack(CombatMusicTrack, 2.0f /* blend duration */);

// Fade in percussion stem when entering intense combat
Sonance-&gt;SetStemWeight(ESonanceStemRole::Percussion, 1.0f, 1.5f);
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <ol> <li>Add <code>USonanceDialogueComponent</code> to your NPC.</li> <li>Call Sonance Dialogue &gt; Play Dialogue Data passing the asset.</li> </ol> <pre><code>#include "Sonance/SonanceDialogueComponent.h"

DialogueComponent-&gt;PlayDialogueData(GreetingDialogueData);

// Bind to completion
DialogueComponent-&gt;OnDialogueComplete.AddDynamic(this, &amp;AMyNPC::HandleDialogueDone);
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <p>Override the Can Add Item event in your Blueprint to implement custom container logic. Return <code>true</code> to allow, <code>false</code> to reject.</p> <pre><code>// Override in your subclass or use the BlueprintNativeEvent
virtual bool CanAddItem_Implementation(const FVaultItemInstance&amp; Item) override;
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <ol> <li>Open your Character, Chest, or Vendor Blueprint.</li> <li>Add Component &gt; VaultContainerComponent.</li> <li>In the Details panel, set:<ul> <li>Mode — <code>SlotBased</code>, <code>WeightBased</code>, <code>SlotAndWeight</code>, or <code>Unlimited</code></li> <li>MaxSlots — maximum item slots (if slot-based)</li> <li>MaxWeight — weight capacity (if weight-based)</li> <li>bStackSimilarItems — whether identical items auto-stack</li> </ul> </li> </ol> <pre><code>#include "VaultContainerComponent.h"

UPROPERTY(VisibleAnywhere, Category = "Inventory")
TObjectPtr&lt;UVaultContainerComponent&gt; Inventory;

// In constructor
Inventory = CreateDefaultSubobject&lt;UVaultContainerComponent&gt;(TEXT("Inventory"));
Inventory-&gt;Mode = EVaultContainerMode::SlotAndWeight;
Inventory-&gt;MaxSlots = 20;
Inventory-&gt;MaxWeight = 100.f;
Inventory-&gt;bStackSimilarItems = true;
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <ol> <li>Get the Vault Subsystem and call Create Item Instance with the item's <code>PrimaryAssetId</code> and quantity.</li> <li>Call Add Item on your <code>VaultContainerComponent</code>, passing the created instance.</li> <li>Check the returned <code>FVaultTransactionResult</code>:<ul> <li>bSuccess — whether the operation succeeded</li> <li>QuantityProcessed / QuantityRejected — how many items were accepted/rejected</li> <li>FailReason — text description if failed</li> </ul> </li> <li>To remove, call Remove Item with the <code>InstanceId</code> and quantity to remove (0 = remove all).</li> </ol> <pre><code>UVaultSubsystem* VaultSub = UVaultSubsystem::Get(this);

// Create an item instance
FPrimaryAssetId SwordPAID(TEXT("VaultItemDefinition"), TEXT("Sword_Iron"));
FVaultItemInstance SwordInstance = VaultSub-&gt;CreateItemInstance(SwordPAID, 3);

// Add to inventory
FVaultTransactionResult Result = Inventory-&gt;AddItem(SwordInstance);

if (Result.bSuccess)
{
    UE_LOG(LogVault, Log, TEXT("Added %d swords"), Result.QuantityProcessed);
}
else
{
    UE_LOG(LogVault, Warning, TEXT("Failed: %s"), *Result.FailReason.ToString());
}

// Remove 1 sword by instance ID
FVaultTransactionResult RemoveResult = Inventory-&gt;RemoveItem(SwordInstance.InstanceId, 1);
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <ol> <li>Call Equip Item on the container with the item's <code>InstanceId</code>.</li> <li>The item gains the "Equipped" runtime tag.</li> <li>If an <code>IVaultEquipmentBridge</code> is set, it validates the equip request first.</li> <li>Call Unequip Item to reverse.</li> </ol> <pre><code>// Equip
FVaultTransactionResult EquipResult = Inventory-&gt;EquipItem(SwordInstance.InstanceId);

// Unequip
FVaultTransactionResult UnequipResult = Inventory-&gt;UnequipItem(SwordInstance.InstanceId);
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <p>Call Use Item with the <code>InstanceId</code> and quantity to consume. The item's quantity decreases; if it reaches zero, the item is removed. The <code>OnItemUsed</code> delegate fires.</p> <pre><code>// Use 1 health potion
FVaultTransactionResult UseResult = Inventory-&gt;UseItem(PotionInstance.InstanceId, 1);
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <ol> <li>Create an <code>FVaultAppliedModifier</code> struct with the modifier's <code>PrimaryAssetId</code>, type tag, and optional instance data.</li> <li>Call Apply Modifier on the container with the item's <code>InstanceId</code>.</li> <li>The modifier is added to the item's modifier list if the item accepts that modifier type and has available slots.</li> </ol> <pre><code>FVaultAppliedModifier FireEnchant;
FireEnchant.ModifierPAID = FPrimaryAssetId(TEXT("VaultModDefinition"), TEXT("Mod_FireDamage"));
FireEnchant.ModifierType = FGameplayTag::RequestGameplayTag(TEXT("Mod.Enchant.Fire"));

FVaultTransactionResult ModResult = Inventory-&gt;ApplyModifier(SwordInstance.InstanceId, FireEnchant);
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <ol> <li>Create a rule asset or instance (e.g., <code>VaultRule_Craft</code>) and configure its inputs and outputs.</li> <li>Call Can Apply Rule from the <code>VaultFunctionLibrary</code> to check prerequisites.</li> <li>Call Apply Rule to execute.</li> </ol> <pre><code>#include "VaultFunctionLibrary.h"

// Check if crafting is possible
if (UVaultFunctionLibrary::CanApplyRule(Inventory, ItemInstanceId, CraftingRule))
{
    FVaultTransactionResult CraftResult = UVaultFunctionLibrary::ApplyRule(
        Inventory, ItemInstanceId, CraftingRule
    );
}
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ Node Description Get All Items Returns all <code>FVaultItemInstance</code> entries in the container Has Item Check if a specific <code>PrimaryAssetId</code> exists Count Item Count total quantity of a specific item Find By Tag Find items matching a gameplay tag Find By PAID Find all instances of a specific definition Get Current Weight Total weight in the container Is Empty / Is Full Container state checks <pre><code>// Get all items
TArray&lt;FVaultItemInstance&gt; AllItems = Inventory-&gt;GetAllItems();

// Check for a specific item
bool bHasSword = Inventory-&gt;HasItem(SwordPAID);
int32 SwordCount = Inventory-&gt;CountItem(SwordPAID);

// Find items by tag
FGameplayTag WeaponTag = FGameplayTag::RequestGameplayTag(TEXT("Item.Weapon"));
TArray&lt;FVaultItemInstance&gt; Weapons = Inventory-&gt;FindByTag(WeaponTag);

// Weight and capacity
float CurrentWeight = Inventory-&gt;GetCurrentWeight();
bool bFull = Inventory-&gt;IsFull();
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <p>In your Blueprint, select the <code>VaultContainerComponent</code> and bind to events in the Details panel:</p> <ul> <li>On Item Added — fires when an item is added</li> <li>On Item Removed — fires when an item is removed</li> <li>On Item Equipped / On Item Unequipped — equip state changes</li> <li>On Item Used — item consumed</li> <li>On Item Modified — modifier applied/removed</li> <li>On Container Full — container rejected an add due to capacity</li> <li>On Transaction Completed — fires for every operation with the full result</li> </ul> <pre><code>// Bind to delegates
Inventory-&gt;OnItemAdded.AddDynamic(this, &amp;AMyCharacter::HandleItemAdded);
Inventory-&gt;OnItemRemoved.AddDynamic(this, &amp;AMyCharacter::HandleItemRemoved);
Inventory-&gt;OnContainerFull.AddDynamic(this, &amp;AMyCharacter::HandleContainerFull);
Inventory-&gt;OnTransactionCompleted.AddDynamic(this, &amp;AMyCharacter::HandleTransaction);

void AMyCharacter::HandleItemAdded(FVaultItemInstance Item)
{
    UpdateInventoryUI();
}
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <ol> <li>Add a VaultTransactionComponent alongside your <code>VaultContainerComponent</code>.</li> <li>Set MaxHistorySize in the Details panel.</li> <li>Call Rollback Last to undo the most recent operation, or Rollback with a specific <code>TransactionId</code>.</li> <li>Call Get History to display a transaction log in your UI.</li> </ol> <pre><code>#include "VaultTransactionComponent.h"

UPROPERTY(VisibleAnywhere)
TObjectPtr&lt;UVaultTransactionComponent&gt; TransactionHistory;

// In constructor
TransactionHistory = CreateDefaultSubobject&lt;UVaultTransactionComponent&gt;(TEXT("TransactionHistory"));
TransactionHistory-&gt;MaxHistorySize = 50;

// Undo last operation
bool bRolledBack = TransactionHistory-&gt;RollbackLast();

// Get full history
const TArray&lt;FVaultTransaction&gt;&amp; Log = TransactionHistory-&gt;GetHistory();
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <p>Use the Vault Function Library load request preset nodes:</p> Preset Loads Load Request World Only World mesh, loot effects Load Request Player Pickup World + UI icons Load Request Player Equip FP First-person + audio Load Request Player Equip Full FP + TP + audio Load Request NPC Equip Third-person + audio Load Request All All tiers <p>Pass the request to your resolver or use <code>GetTierSoftPaths</code> / <code>GetTierPAIDs</code> to get asset references for loading.</p> <pre><code>#include "VaultFunctionLibrary.h"

// Get a preset request
FVaultLoadRequest Request = FVaultLoadRequest::PlayerEquipFP();

// Get soft paths for a specific tier
TArray&lt;FSoftObjectPath&gt; FPPaths = UVaultFunctionLibrary::GetTierSoftPaths(ItemDef, EVaultLoadTier::FirstPerson);

// Check if a tier has data
bool bHasWorldMesh = UVaultFunctionLibrary::HasTierData(ItemDef, EVaultLoadTier::World);
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <ol> <li>Create a Blueprint implementing <code>IVaultResolver</code>.</li> <li>Override Resolve Item, Is Resolved, and Unresolve Item.</li> <li>On BeginPlay, call Set Resolver on the Vault Subsystem.</li> </ol> <pre><code>// Set up the resolver bridge
UVaultSubsystem* VaultSub = UVaultSubsystem::Get(this);
VaultSub-&gt;SetResolver(MyManifestResolverObject);
</code></pre>

BlueprintC++ <p>Have your actor Blueprint implement <code>IVaultContainerNotify</code>. Override On Vault Item Added, On Vault Item Removed, and On Vault Container Full — these fire automatically without binding delegates.</p> <pre><code>class AMyChest : public AActor, public IVaultContainerNotify
{
    virtual void OnVaultItemAdded_Implementation(const FVaultItemInstance&amp; Item) override
    {
        PlayLootDepositEffect();
    }
};
</code></pre>

C++Blueprint <pre><code>#include "WorldPool/WorldPoolSubsystem.h"

UWorldPoolSubsystem* Pool = GetWorld()-&gt;GetSubsystem&lt;UWorldPoolSubsystem&gt;();

// Register a pool for enemy actors
Pool-&gt;RegisterClassPool(ANPCEnemy::StaticClass(), /* pool size */ 64);

// Register a pool for debris props
Pool-&gt;RegisterClassPool(ADebrisProp::StaticClass(), 128);
</code></pre> <p>Call World Pool &gt; Register Class Pool in Begin Play with the actor class and pool size.</p>
